1
00:00:37,880 --> 00:00:39,000
They're going to tear down Commoners' Alley

2
00:00:39,640 --> 00:00:42,719
To build a huge entertainment and shopping complex

3
00:00:42,759 --> 00:00:44,840
Those residents have caused a lot of trouble

4
00:00:45,560 --> 00:00:46,759
Go deal with it

5
00:00:51,280 --> 00:00:52,079
If they tear it down...

6
00:00:52,079 --> 00:00:53,200
Where are we supposed to live?

7
00:00:53,920 --> 00:00:56,439
Mom, if the contract's unfair, we won't sign it

8
00:00:56,759 --> 00:00:57,719
He didn't mention

9
00:00:57,719 --> 00:00:59,000
any relocation or compensation

10
00:00:59,119 --> 00:01:00,399
They're obviously bullying us

11
00:01:01,920 --> 00:01:03,560
Ordinary people like us

12
00:01:03,719 --> 00:01:05,040
what can we even do?

13
00:01:05,319 --> 00:01:07,400
We just have to do whatever they say

14
00:01:07,599 --> 00:01:08,319
No, that won't do

15
00:01:08,840 --> 00:01:10,680
If it's ours, we must fight for it

16
00:01:18,439 --> 00:01:19,359
Without an appointment,

17
00:01:19,359 --> 00:01:21,040
the Chairman usually doesn't see visitors

18
00:01:21,680 --> 00:01:22,760
But about Commoners' Alley,

19
00:01:22,760 --> 00:01:23,680
he's taken it very seriously

20
00:01:31,760 --> 00:01:33,799
Why does this place look so familiar?

21
00:01:41,120 --> 00:01:42,280
Wait here for a moment

22
00:01:42,280 --> 00:01:43,159
The Chairman is taking a bath

23
00:01:43,159 --> 00:01:44,280
He'll be down soon

24
00:01:44,719 --> 00:01:45,359
Okay

25
00:01:50,200 --> 00:01:51,799
Bring me a cup of Egyptian hibiscus tea

26
00:01:55,040 --> 00:01:55,760
Please wait a moment

27
00:01:56,719 --> 00:01:58,640
Why is his taste exactly like the Young Master's?

28
00:02:06,799 --> 00:02:08,280
Have I been here before?

29
00:02:24,080 --> 00:02:25,439
You have good taste

30
00:03:08,520 --> 00:03:09,240
Who are you?

31
00:03:21,199 --> 00:03:23,080
Who are you? Why are you here?

32
00:03:25,479 --> 00:03:26,280
I...

33
00:03:33,960 --> 00:03:35,800
I'm here on behalf of Commoners' Alley

34
00:03:37,159 --> 00:03:37,879
I came to...

35
00:03:44,319 --> 00:03:45,199
What did you say?

36
00:03:46,719 --> 00:03:48,240
N-no, nothing

37
00:04:01,439 --> 00:04:02,560
This is the tea he asked for

38
00:04:02,639 --> 00:04:03,000
Yes

39
00:04:31,759 --> 00:04:32,399
Son

40
00:04:33,160 --> 00:04:33,839
Hello?

41
00:04:34,079 --> 00:04:35,720
Mom, I...

42
00:04:36,199 --> 00:04:37,160
What's wrong with your voice?

43
00:04:37,759 --> 00:04:39,000
Are you feeling sick?

44
00:04:39,399 --> 00:04:40,160
I feel awful

45
00:04:41,279 --> 00:04:42,160
Where are you?

46
00:04:43,480 --> 00:04:44,120
I'm at...

47
00:04:53,720 --> 00:04:54,560
Xiaobei!

48
00:04:55,680 --> 00:04:56,800
Xiaobei!

49
00:04:58,240 --> 00:04:59,319
Xiaobei!

50
00:05:00,120 --> 00:05:01,000
Xiaobei!

51
00:05:03,240 --> 00:05:04,000
Xiaobei!

52
00:05:06,279 --> 00:05:07,879
Xiaobei! Xiaobei!

53
00:05:09,319 --> 00:05:10,240
Mom's here

54
00:05:11,600 --> 00:05:12,399
Xiaobei!

55
00:05:13,560 --> 00:05:14,279
Xiaobei!

56
00:05:14,399 --> 00:05:15,240
Don't be scared

57
00:05:15,800 --> 00:05:16,680
Mom's right here

58
00:05:16,839 --> 00:05:17,720
It's okay now

59
00:05:20,360 --> 00:05:20,920
Mom

60
00:05:22,639 --> 00:05:23,839
Don't leave me

61
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:25,720
Mom will never leave you

62
00:05:30,399 --> 00:05:32,680
This was signed by someone named Zhang Xiaobei

63
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:34,360
It was delivered this afternoon

64
00:05:37,480 --> 00:05:40,439
Didn't expect Sheng Yuanzhou to protest for Commoners' Alley

65
00:05:44,959 --> 00:05:46,480
Do you two have a plan?

66
00:05:47,360 --> 00:05:48,399
This is easy

67
00:05:48,879 --> 00:05:50,560
Hire some guys to beat them up, and they'll behave

68
00:05:51,040 --> 00:05:51,720
That's a bad idea

69
00:05:52,519 --> 00:05:55,639
Commoners' Alley residents are protesting together

70
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:56,920
They're united as one

71
00:05:56,920 --> 00:05:58,079
and facing us together

72
00:05:58,439 --> 00:05:59,480
If at a time like this

73
00:05:59,480 --> 00:06:00,680
we use violence against them,

74
00:06:01,360 --> 00:06:03,199
it'll only make them push back harder

75
00:06:03,199 --> 00:06:04,800
If it blows up, it won't be good for us

76
00:06:04,879 --> 00:06:05,600
It'll be hard to clean up

77
00:06:09,199 --> 00:06:10,279
Tell me what you think

78
00:06:11,040 --> 00:06:12,879
A small leak will sink a great ship.

79
00:06:13,480 --> 00:06:16,079
Ants that swarm together are the toughest to deal with

80
00:06:16,480 --> 00:06:18,040
We should, from the very start,

81
00:06:18,519 --> 00:06:20,319
break them apart from the inside

82
00:06:20,639 --> 00:06:22,199
and wipe out the whole nest

83
00:06:31,160 --> 00:06:32,560
I'm leaving this to you

84
00:06:32,639 --> 00:06:33,879
Show me what you can do

85
00:06:35,120 --> 00:06:35,879
Yes, Father

86
00:07:05,639 --> 00:07:07,120
Careful the ants don't crawl onto you

87
00:07:07,639 --> 00:07:08,439
and become impossible to shake off

88
00:07:11,199 --> 00:07:12,120
Don't worry, Father

89
00:07:12,519 --> 00:07:14,000
I won't let you down

90
00:07:26,720 --> 00:07:27,639
Let's not stand around here

91
00:07:27,639 --> 00:07:28,879
wasting each other's time

92
00:07:29,600 --> 00:07:30,279
This land,

93
00:07:30,759 --> 00:07:32,279
the Sheng family is determined to get

94
00:07:32,639 --> 00:07:34,319
Our terms are already in black and white,

95
00:07:34,319 --> 00:07:35,439
written crystal clear

96
00:07:35,639 --> 00:07:36,480
There's no negotiating

97
00:07:37,279 --> 00:07:38,120
Zhang Xiaobei

98
00:07:38,759 --> 00:07:40,279
If you aren't just naive,

99
00:07:40,519 --> 00:07:41,959
then you're incredibly stupid

100
00:07:42,040 --> 00:07:44,839
You really think a few lousy papers

101
00:07:44,920 --> 00:07:46,120
give you the right to make wild demands?

102
00:07:46,680 --> 00:07:47,879
You tenants

103
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:50,160
aren't even covered by compensation

104
00:07:51,319 --> 00:07:52,560
I've read the contract

105
00:07:52,639 --> 00:07:54,120
We're long-term tenants

106
00:07:54,240 --> 00:07:55,399
The sale does not break the lease

107
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:56,800
You have no right to

108
00:07:56,800 --> 00:07:57,959
force us out

109
00:07:57,959 --> 00:07:59,959
Our demand for extra compensation

110
00:07:59,959 --> 00:08:00,759
is fair and reasonable

111
00:08:01,040 --> 00:08:03,680
It's clearly written in the contract,

112
00:08:04,959 --> 00:08:06,519
all tenants in Commoners' Alley,

113
00:08:06,560 --> 00:08:08,120
after the complex is built,

114
00:08:08,600 --> 00:08:10,319
can sign a lease

115
00:08:10,439 --> 00:08:12,279
at a discounted rate

116
00:08:14,360 --> 00:08:15,839
That's the compensation I'm offering

117
00:08:16,319 --> 00:08:17,480
Are you kidding me?

118
00:08:18,439 --> 00:08:20,079
How are we supposed to settle down for the next few years?

119
00:08:20,079 --> 00:08:21,279
Do you think the people living here

120
00:08:21,279 --> 00:08:22,800
can afford to move into that complex?

121
00:08:22,879 --> 00:08:24,600
So you want to use the demolition

122
00:08:24,839 --> 00:08:26,439
to extort us for a windfall, huh?

123
00:08:26,720 --> 00:08:27,759
I'll say it again

124
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:29,560
Our demands are fair and reasonable

125
00:08:29,600 --> 00:08:31,519
If you won't raise the extra compensation,

126
00:08:31,519 --> 00:08:32,480
none of us

127
00:08:32,480 --> 00:08:34,639
will sign the demolition consent form

128
00:08:34,639 --> 00:08:35,159
Is that so?

129
00:08:35,320 --> 00:08:36,159
Xiaobei

130
00:08:37,120 --> 00:08:37,679
Xiaobei!

131
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:39,639
A lot of neighbors

132
00:08:39,960 --> 00:08:41,279
are getting ready to sign

133
00:08:41,279 --> 00:08:41,879
What?

134
00:08:42,919 --> 00:08:44,720
They said there's some kind of bonus

135
00:08:44,919 --> 00:08:47,159
The earlier you sign, the more you get

136
00:08:47,480 --> 00:08:48,879
I didn't really catch the details

137
00:08:49,080 --> 00:08:50,039
It's an incentive scheme

138
00:08:50,320 --> 00:08:53,000
It specially rewards residents who cooperate

139
00:08:53,679 --> 00:08:56,600
The bonus decreases the later you sign

140
00:08:56,799 --> 00:08:57,519
That means

141
00:08:57,519 --> 00:08:59,120
the first resident to sign willingly

142
00:08:59,519 --> 00:09:01,720
gets the biggest special bonus

143
00:09:01,919 --> 00:09:02,519
On the other hand,

144
00:09:02,519 --> 00:09:03,639
the last person to sign

145
00:09:04,519 --> 00:09:05,759
won't get a cent

146
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:07,600
You're trying to turn us against each other

147
00:09:07,840 --> 00:09:08,559
Let me tell you

148
00:09:08,559 --> 00:09:10,240
This is human greed

149
00:09:10,519 --> 00:09:11,720
Once they think

150
00:09:11,720 --> 00:09:13,960
they can get even a little more than others,

151
00:09:14,200 --> 00:09:15,639
they'll cling to it and never let go

152
00:09:15,639 --> 00:09:16,399
Given this chance,

153
00:09:16,879 --> 00:09:17,559
just watch

154
00:09:18,080 --> 00:09:19,080
Starting now,

155
00:09:19,200 --> 00:09:22,440
they'll fight tooth and nail to sign

156
00:09:22,519 --> 00:09:23,279
Then,

157
00:09:23,679 --> 00:09:24,519
your Zhang family

158
00:09:24,840 --> 00:09:27,279
will be the sole holdout in Commoners' Alley

159
00:09:28,919 --> 00:09:30,840
So what the Shengs do best

160
00:09:30,840 --> 00:09:32,120
is twisting the truth

161
00:09:32,279 --> 00:09:33,639
Let me give you a way out

162
00:09:34,320 --> 00:09:35,200
Be the first to sign

163
00:09:36,120 --> 00:09:37,919
For old classmates' sake,

164
00:09:38,159 --> 00:09:40,480
I'll put that top bonus

165
00:09:40,759 --> 00:09:41,919
under your name

166
00:09:42,279 --> 00:09:43,200
No way

167
00:09:44,120 --> 00:09:45,120
In your dreams

168
00:09:49,080 --> 00:09:51,200
A wise man adapts to circumstances.

169
00:09:51,679 --> 00:09:52,879
You're not a savior

170
00:09:53,159 --> 00:09:54,360
Save your own family first

171
00:09:54,759 --> 00:09:57,200
I'm not gonna hide like a coward

172
00:09:57,320 --> 00:09:59,840
What's mine, I'll take back

173
00:10:00,120 --> 00:10:01,320
I'll give you one day

174
00:10:02,519 --> 00:10:03,799
to think it over

175
00:10:04,519 --> 00:10:05,159
Auntie,

176
00:10:05,879 --> 00:10:07,039
you should talk some sense into Zhang Xiaobei

177
00:10:07,519 --> 00:10:08,399
Save yourselves first

178
00:10:08,799 --> 00:10:09,879
The demolition of Commoners' Alley

179
00:10:10,360 --> 00:10:11,759
is impossible to stop

180
00:10:11,919 --> 00:10:12,840
Be the first to sign,

181
00:10:12,840 --> 00:10:13,639
and that 100,000 yuan

182
00:10:13,840 --> 00:10:15,200
will count as my compensation to you

183
00:10:15,360 --> 00:10:15,960
Get out

184
00:10:16,480 --> 00:10:17,519
I only listen to my son

185
00:10:30,080 --> 00:10:32,279
Xiaobei, what do we do now?

186
00:10:33,120 --> 00:10:33,559
Mom

187
00:10:34,159 --> 00:10:35,440
We need to go talk to the neighbors

188
00:10:35,480 --> 00:10:36,799
We have to stick together on this

189
00:10:37,480 --> 00:10:38,639
Xiaobei, your dad...

190
00:10:38,759 --> 00:10:39,519
Something happened to your dad!

191
00:10:46,279 --> 00:10:47,840
Mr. Sheng, take a look at this

192
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:53,360
A riot broke out in Commoners' Alley

193
00:10:53,519 --> 00:10:54,480
It started because residents

194
00:10:54,480 --> 00:10:56,240
couldn't agree about the demolition

195
00:10:56,399 --> 00:10:57,639
A verbal argument

196
00:10:57,639 --> 00:10:59,919
escalated into a bloody brawl

197
00:11:00,039 --> 00:11:01,679
The number of injured is still unknown

198
00:11:01,720 --> 00:11:03,399
Police have already launched an investigation

199
00:11:10,200 --> 00:11:12,240
The number you dialed is powered off

200
00:11:16,279 --> 00:11:17,720
Doctor, please save my dad!

201
00:11:17,960 --> 00:11:18,559
He's hurt!

202
00:11:18,559 --> 00:11:19,279
Stop yelling!

203
00:11:19,399 --> 00:11:20,480
Can't you see how many people are here?

204
00:11:20,600 --> 00:11:21,240
Get in line

205
00:11:26,120 --> 00:11:27,000
Okay, I got it

206
00:11:27,440 --> 00:11:28,600
Young Master Sheng arranged

207
00:11:28,600 --> 00:11:29,919
a private doctor and a room for you

208
00:11:30,120 --> 00:11:30,720
This way, please

209
00:11:40,679 --> 00:11:41,519
How did he get hurt?

210
00:11:41,799 --> 00:11:43,879
Someone shoved him, and he hit his head

211
00:11:45,159 --> 00:11:46,120
All right, I understand

212
00:11:54,639 --> 00:11:55,720
How'd he get hurt this badly?

213
00:11:55,720 --> 00:11:57,360
Cut the Crocodile tears

214
00:11:57,440 --> 00:11:58,679
Get out of here. Now!

215
00:11:58,679 --> 00:11:59,159
Wait

216
00:12:00,480 --> 00:12:01,519
When your dad recovers,

217
00:12:01,879 --> 00:12:02,720
I'll leave on my own

218
00:12:03,120 --> 00:12:05,200
Isn't my dad like this because of you?

219
00:12:05,320 --> 00:12:06,240
Forget it, Xiaobei

220
00:12:06,679 --> 00:12:08,559
He found a doctor for us

221
00:12:08,799 --> 00:12:09,720
and helped us out

222
00:12:09,720 --> 00:12:10,919
Mom, don't believe him

223
00:12:11,120 --> 00:12:12,639
Our family's in this mess because of him!

224
00:12:13,240 --> 00:12:14,240
Get out, you hear me?

225
00:12:14,480 --> 00:12:15,080
Get out!

226
00:12:16,200 --> 00:12:16,799
Hurry up!

227
00:12:17,039 --> 00:12:17,919
Xiaobei

228
00:12:18,080 --> 00:12:18,919
Get out of here, now

229
00:12:20,480 --> 00:12:22,960
I honestly had no idea about what happened today

230
00:12:33,679 --> 00:12:34,519
Where did this come from?

231
00:12:34,759 --> 00:12:36,320
Didn't you have someone send it to Commoners' Alley?

232
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:38,720
My dad got beaten because of this

233
00:12:40,240 --> 00:12:41,039
Explain yourself

234
00:12:41,320 --> 00:12:42,159
Explain!

235
00:12:42,919 --> 00:12:43,360
Fine

236
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:45,559
Then I'll spell it out for you today

237
00:12:46,159 --> 00:12:47,519
You sent people with a home purchase contract

238
00:12:47,519 --> 00:12:48,679
to our place, shouting it everywhere

239
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:51,519
They said we protest in public for justice,

240
00:12:51,840 --> 00:12:53,559
but secretly ask the Sheng family for favors

241
00:12:53,559 --> 00:12:54,480
And even took an apartment

242
00:12:54,720 --> 00:12:55,639
My dad tried to explain to them,

243
00:12:55,639 --> 00:12:56,639
and then he got beaten

244
00:12:56,799 --> 00:12:58,480
And this is what turned it into a riot

245
00:12:58,639 --> 00:13:00,159
At first, it was just a few people yelling

246
00:13:00,360 --> 00:13:01,519
Then a group of guys in black showed up

247
00:13:01,519 --> 00:13:02,799
They swung sticks and beat people everywhere

248
00:13:02,960 --> 00:13:03,799
After that, it got even worse

249
00:13:05,159 --> 00:13:07,320
That had to be people Sheng Shizhong sent

250
00:13:08,799 --> 00:13:09,320
Tell me

251
00:13:10,120 --> 00:13:11,440
Did you buy the place for us on purpose,

252
00:13:11,440 --> 00:13:12,559
then frame us for it,

253
00:13:12,679 --> 00:13:13,919
so you could profit from the mess?

254
00:13:16,759 --> 00:13:17,759
Calm down

255
00:13:19,200 --> 00:13:20,360
I proposed the bonus

256
00:13:20,799 --> 00:13:22,919
just to prevent bloodshed

257
00:13:23,200 --> 00:13:23,639
Prevent?

258
00:13:24,399 --> 00:13:25,919
Look at how badly my dad's hurt!

259
00:13:26,679 --> 00:13:28,440
Stop putting on an act in front of me

260
00:13:28,759 --> 00:13:29,759
You did it on purpose!

261
00:13:29,960 --> 00:13:31,639
Get out! Get out of here, now!

262
00:13:34,279 --> 00:13:36,480
Regarding the Commoners' Alley riot,

263
00:13:36,519 --> 00:13:38,759
our station conducted an exclusive interview

264
00:13:38,759 --> 00:13:39,639
with Prosperity Group Chairman Sheng Shizhong

265
00:13:39,879 --> 00:13:41,080
Renovating the old district

266
00:13:41,200 --> 00:13:43,440
is meant to improve everyone's living conditions

267
00:13:43,639 --> 00:13:45,679
and create more jobs

268
00:13:45,960 --> 00:13:46,919
But some people

269
00:13:47,080 --> 00:13:49,399
took it as a chance to get rich overnight,

270
00:13:49,799 --> 00:13:52,519
and to get more benefits than others,

271
00:13:52,639 --> 00:13:53,600
they came to blows

272
00:13:53,799 --> 00:13:56,080
In the end, it caused bloodshed

273
00:13:56,480 --> 00:13:57,399
Seeing it,

274
00:13:57,559 --> 00:13:59,200
I am deeply distressed
